ive identities based on Islamic commonality. Instead of the certainties of the nation-states that emerged in the wake of the belated peace treaty of 1923, we see how the Ottoman empire remained central in the mindset of leaders and popular groups with long-lasting consequences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 7aHISTORY / Middle East / Turkey & Ottoman Empire.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073915240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052097510140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520975101423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520975101/original  a978-3-11-073915-2  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles